    "summary": "Lisette Gast is a freelance consultant with over twenty years of work experience in the facilitation of complex change processes, often based on participatory monitoring and evaluation systems. With an academic background in communications, Ms. Gast gained experience with many facets of project and programme development in many countries, a.o. Tanzania, Ecuador, Colombia, Bolivia, Ghana and Jordan. \nDuring her career she developed a passion for the working for and with Women and Child Rights initiatives. \n\nLisette has designed and facilitated a range of processes, which include design and implementation of trainings, setting up monitoring evaluations systems, coaching and external evaluations. \nShe strongly supports participatory learning processes, where the participants in a workshop and training are challenged to reflect and are enabled to work on knowledge skills and attitudes.\n\nLisette is takes inspiration by group dynamics in complex settings and is always curious to gain new insights. She is has an open and energetic personality.\n\nLisette is partner and co-founder of Perspectivity Enterprise.",
